Please follow the instructions in the notice. If you have any questions, contact the USCIS Contact Center at www.uscis.gov/contactcenter. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

title: Notice Was Returned To USCIS Because The Post Office Could Not Deliver It
body: On March 16, 2021, the Post Office returned a notice we sent you for your Form I-765, Application for Employment Authorization, Receipt Number YSC2190073993, because they could not deliver it. This could have a serious effect on your case. Please go to www.uscis.gov/e-request to request a copy of the notice immediately. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

title: Card Was Mailed To Me
body: On March 19, 2021, we mailed your new card for your Form I-765, Application for Employment Authorization, Receipt Number YSC2190073994, to the address you gave us. If you do not receive your card by April 3, 2021, please go to www.uscis.gov/e-request to request that we send your new card to you. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.
